FOLLOWING STATE PLANS:
(I) THE STATE RESILIENCE STRATEGY, AS DESCRIBED IN §
14–1202 OF THE PUBLIC SAFETY ARTICLE; AND
(II) THE STATE OF MARYLAND HAZARD MITIGATION PLAN, AS
REQUIRED UNDER 44 C.F.R. PART 201.
(2) THE DEPARTMENT OF PLANNING SHALL:
(I) PROVIDE A LOCAL JURISDICTION WITH THE BEST
AVAILABLE POPULATION, DEMOGRAPHIC, ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, AND HOUSING
DATA FROM THE U.S. CENSUS BUREAU AND OTHER STANDARD SOURCES; AND
(II) FACILITATE, TO THE EXTENT POSSIBLE, THE PROVISION OF
DATA RELEVANT TO THE PREPARATION OF THE RESILIENCE ELEMENT FROM OTHER
STATE AGENCIES.
