MITIGATE RISKS TO PUBLIC SAFETY, CRITICAL INFRASTRUCTURE, HISTORIC
STRUCTURES, PUBLIC INVESTMENTS, AND OTHER COMMUNITY RESOURCES; AND
(II) THAT ARE INTENDED TO:
1. REDUCE RISKS ASSOCIATED WITH IDENTIFIED
HAZARDS;
2. ADAPT TO CHANGING CONDITIONS; AND
3. PROMOTE QUICKER RECOVERY AFTER A DISASTER.
